Set up Reth Execution client and Lighthouse Consensus clientAfter both the clients have synced we will setup an execution extension(ExEx)ExEx is configured such that it indexes the data received from the node by the conditions that we specify and registers it in a sql databaseExEx are post-execution hooks designed for building off chain infrastructure on top of Reth. It is an async function consuming the Reth's state.indexed data is stored in the database and is ready to be served to the frontend through the backendIndexing from local nodeUser enters the request through frontendThe request is passed to the backend and then calls the api to the RPC node with the required dataAfter the data is processed it is stored in a sql databaseIndexing from a RPC nodedata is transmitted to the front end in form of JSON which is available for consumption of end user
